  "title": "Allow combining in hierarchicalMenu",
  "body": "Based on the v2 docs I created a menu with 1 sublevel.\r\n\r\n![screen shot 2018-04-05 at 2 10 40 pm](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3603346/38365052-2a8113ca-38db-11e8-8b33-4c45bac198f2.png)\r\n\r\nWorks so far. What I'd like to accomplish now is that I can select multiple menu items together (e.g. \"Experten\" and \"Zentren\"). Is this something I can do with the current API? If so, how? I could not find anything helpful.\r\n\r\nAlso, how can I sort the lvl0 list (maybe even manually) different to the lvl1 items (need to be name:asc).\r\n\r\n![screen shot 2018-04-05 at 2 14 20 pm](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3603346/38365193-aa2f927c-38db-11e8-9edf-165c881686f4.png)\r\n",
